6:
Hwaa-ha-haa!

Bow before the Lord of Scarecrows,
Regitare!
9:
Look, a skeleton! C'mon everybody,
let's get him!
12:
Looks like they're having a
topsy-turvy good time!
22:
Wrong holiday for spooky skellies,
but seeing as the kids are having a
blast, I'll overlook the cackling.
25:
It's not every day you see a prancing
skeleton, though. How is it able to do
that?
30: Uh... The power of magic...? Maybe?
33:
Oh, is he a friend of yours Alk? Guess
that makes sense, then!
37:
Alk! Stella! Come quick! The tree isn't
feeling so good!
41:
The tree...? Oh, you mean the
holiday tree?
43:
Actually, a mob of monsters came
crashing through not too long ago.
The poor tree hasn't been the same
since.
44:
Maybe... It's feeling under the
weather.
49:
Then it needs to stay hydrated and
get plenty of rest.
52:
Hmm. I'd love to do that, but it's
already decorated, and finding
another holiday tree on such short
notice might be difficult...
53:
I'm sorry. I wish there was something
I could do.
57:
I know how you feel, child, but this
tree doesn't belong to our forest. I'm
afraid there's not much we can do
either.
68:
Grrrgh!

I didn't know... reindeer... have
it—*wheeze*... have it so tough!
72:
Nrrrgh! Just keep pulling!

I don't know how much longer I'll
last...
75: You can do it! Just one more push!
79:
Okay! You can stop here! Thank you
so much!
83:
Phew... You sure here's all right? Not
that I'm complaining—I'm beat after
lugging this thing.
86:
But heck, I didn't think you had it in
you to kidnap a tree. You've got
guts, Challua!
91:
I didn't kidnap. I came here to ask for
a favor.
107:
I speak as a child of the forest and
Spirit Tree!
109:
Hear my voice! Listen to my wish!

Inheritors of the forest's will, answer
me!
113:
Those words... Are they an
incantation?
125:
Would anyone here like to be a
holiday tree?
132:
Is it just me, or is there something
different about this tree...?
137:
Haha... Maybe it's just your
imagination?
144:
Speaking of which... We got reports
last night of some tree-like monster
walking around the outskirts of
Palpebra. You wouldn't know
anything about that, would you?
149: I-is that right? Can't say I do...
152:
And the adventurers who were sent
out to deal with it had a run-in with
a masked tiger-man.
157:
Gotta be careful. You never know
what's lurking in those woods, huh.
163:
Ohh, you know that I'm the one who
has to clean up after you, right?!
167:
What kind of trouble did you get into
in my absence?
175:
Challua is a troublemaker!
Troublemaking is so much fun!
